article.description: Kris Martin nailed 5 of 8 from beyond the arc for 17 points to lead Oral Roberts to its second win of the season, a 95-63 victory over NAIA John Brown on Saturday.
article.headline: Oral Roberts gets 2nd win, beats NAIA John Brown 95-63
article.linkText: Oral Roberts gets 2nd win, beats NAIA John Brown 95-63
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Kris Martin nailed 5 of 8 from beyond the arc for 17 points to lead Oral Roberts to its second win of the season, a 95-63 victory over NAIA John Brown on Saturday. Oral Roberts (2-8) had lost seven straight prior to knocking off John Brown. Jalen Bradley made 6 of 11 field goal attempts for 15 points, Albert Owens added 14, Chris Miller had 12 and Jontray Harris chipped in 11 as 11 ORU players got on the scoreboard. The Golden Eagles stayed hot through the game, hitting 61.5 percent from the floor and making 15 of 25 (60 percent) from long range. ORU, which led 49-30 at the break, shot 63.6 percent from the floor in the first half and made 7 of 13 from beyond the arc. Ricky Roberts led John Brown with 13 points.
